A new release of Cantera is now available, which contains some
significant new capabilities. A platform-independent graphical tool
(&#39;MixMaster&#39;) is included that provides point-and-click access to some
of Cantera&#39;s features, including chemical equilibrium and reaction path
diagrams. 

For a brief overview of the current release, take a look at the
Powerpoint presentations:
http://blue.caltech.edu/cantera_dist/doc/mixmaster.pps
http://blue.caltech.edu/cantera_dist/doc/cantera_intro.pps
Additional documentation will follow.

The release is packaged as a CD for Win32 PCs. Cantera and all packages
it requires can be installed on a PC by simply running &#39;setup.bat&#39; on
the installation CD. 

Download the entire installation CD as a zip file (11 Mb) here:
http://blue.caltech.edu/cantera_dist/1.3.5/Cantera_CD.zip

Or get individual components here
http://blue.caltech.edu/cantera_dist/1.3.5/CD

 The current release is configured for PCs, but it runs just as well on
linux. A linux version will be added shortly, and perhaps one for Mac OS
10.

The released source code has not yet been updated to reflect the new
features, but soon will be.


